column7: Symptom 1: Please see CAPA40 for board level failure symptoms. Symptom 2: Purchasing can not purchase Xilinx FPGA 040618, Allegro Microsystems PWM Motor Driver IC 040614 and Texas Instruments Switch Regulator Module 040716.  Root Cause 1: Please see Engineering Qualification Form EQF_065121-1 attached to REA and in the DMS project folder. Root Cause 2: Manufacturers have marked these components as obsolete with no direct drop in replacements.  Solution 1: Please see Engineering Qualification Form EQF_065121-1 attached to REA and in the DMS project folder. Solution 2: Re-design PCBA 039441 to use newer components and take care of CAPA40 issues. Re-name and re-number PCBA because of backwards compatibility issues.    Note 1 FOR SERVICE: Due to added circuitry and protection
column8: physical board size had to grow. Please see EQF for all appropriate approvals. Because form changed this new design is not backwards compatible. Re-number and re-name of board is 065121-1 ZOOM 12 OIB to replace 039441 FF OIB and 065121-2 ZOOM 12 OIB REMOTE LEDS to replace 039443 FF OIB W/O LEDs.  Note 2 FOR SERVICE: Service will have to generate service bulletins for any replacement of a 039441 or 039443 into a machine that only used these boards for DRS Laser Mechanical Limits. Due to the board size increase there are some fitment issues. With the help of Mechanical Engineering a solution was found to install the PCBA into the arm by drilling 4 holes and using the existing hardware. Any replacement into a Zoom 12X optics machine will not require any modifications or extra hardware.  Note 3 FOR SERVICE and PLANNING: New fish paper (041237) will have to be sent out with any 065121-1 or 065121-2 being sent out for service replacement. 065121-1 replaces 039441. 065121-2 replaces 039443. 041237 replaces 525891.  Note 4 FOR Custom Engineering (CEG): 039441 and 039443 are obsolete and replaced by 065121-1 and 065121-2 respectively.

column7: Initial Release.  The following serial numbers were pre-production units that are labeled 065121-1 REV.A and the bare PCB is labeled 039440 REV.F (in copper) and the silk screen has the title of “PCB- FLASH/FLARE INTERCONNECT BD”. These PCBAs have been reworked and are acceptable to use in production machines. S/N:QVI0001, QVI0003, QVI0004, QVI0005 and QVI0006. These five boards are with Ian.  Production 065121-1 REV.A PCBAs have the correct PCB part number and correct silk screen per the print.
